    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing fields in copy_harq_proc_struct function\n\n### Summary\nThe `copy_harq_proc_struct` function in the UE PHY procedures was not copying all fields from the source HARQ process structure to the destination. This led to inconsistent behavior when the function was called, as some fields in the destination structure retained uninitialized or stale values.\n\nSpecifically, the following fields were not being copied:\n- RTC array (RTC values for each segment)\n- c array (pointers to transport block segments)  \n- d array (pointers to soft bits for each received segment)\n- w array (soft bits for each received segment)\n- w_abs array (abstraction soft bits for each received segment)\n- trials array (trials per round statistics)\n- errors array (error statistics per round)\n\nThis could cause issues during HARQ retransmissions or when accessing these fields in different threads, as the values would not match between the source and destination structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED_UE/phy_procedures_lte_ue.c`: Updated the `copy_harq_proc_struct` function to copy all missing fields from the source to destination HARQ process structures. Added loops to properly copy all elements of the RTC, c, d, w, w_abs, trials, and errors arrays.\n"
}